dcterms:description: The Science News dataset contains 1042 scientific news articles classified into eight fields: Anthropology, Astronomy, Behavioral Sciences, Earth Sciences, Life Sciences, Math/CS, Medicine, and Physics. Each article is tagged with keywords from a pool of 1133 words selected by the database curators.
dcterms:title: Science News Dataset

dcterms:description: The rMD17 dataset contains 100,000 structures and associated energies of various molecules, taken from a molecular dynamics simulation. The dataset is used for predicting the potential energy surface of a molecule.
dcterms:title: rMD17 Dataset

dcterms:creator: P. Yanardag
S. V. N. Vishwanathan
dcterms:description: The Google Collab dataset is a collaboration dataset of 5K scientific papers represented as graphs. The goal is to predict which of three subfields a paper belongs to given its authors.
dcterms:title: Google Collab Dataset

dcterms:creator: P. D. Dobson
A. J. Doig
dcterms:description: The DD dataset consists of 1178 molecular graphs of medium to large size, used to predict whether the protein is an enzyme or not.
dcterms:title: DD Dataset

dcterms:creator: P. Yanardag
S. V. N. Vishwanathan
dcterms:description: The IMDB-B dataset represents collaboration within popular movies from the Internet Movie Database with 1K graphs, used to predict the genre of the movies.
dcterms:title: IMDB-B Dataset

dcterms:creator: P. Yanardag
S. V. N. Vishwanathan
dcterms:description: The IMDB-M dataset is similar to IMDB-B but contains 1.5k graphs, used to predict the genre of movies.
dcterms:title: IMDB-M Dataset

dcterms:description: The MUTAG dataset consists of 188 molecular graphs representing mutagenic aromatic and heteroaromatic nitro compounds, used to predict whether a molecule has a mutagenic effect.
dcterms:title: MUTAG Dataset
